Jan. 13, 2003 Vol.6, No.2 
TO VIEW THIS EMAIL IN IT'S INTENDED FORMAT, PLEASE CUT AND PASTE THE
FOLLOWING TEXT INTO YOUR BROWSER:
http://www.eschoolnews.com/alert/jan13alert.htm


"The weekly newsletter for K-12 technology decision makers"
 Get Alert every week--FREE! 
http://www.eschoolnews.com/alert/jan13alert.htm 

 
NEWS ALERT ...
Report: States need more money, guidance to improve schools
Lack of money and delayed guidelines from the federal government are
undermining states’ efforts to comply with the year-old school-reform law
that promises to "leave no child behind," according to a study released
Jan. 3 by the Center on Education Policy, a think tank that advocates and
studies public education....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/news/showStoryalert.cfm?ArticleID=4191 

 
GRANT ALERT ... 
$3 million in matching grants to NABSE school districts
PLATO Learning Inc. will award a total of $3 million in matching grants to
school districts affiliated with the National Alliance of Black School
Educators (NABSE). The goal of the grant is to document how a
research-based technology strategy can help implement the strategic
changes required by No Child Left Behind Act of 2001, address state
assessments, and increase overall school improvement....
Deadline: Jan. 20
http://www.eschoolnews.com/resources/funding/opps.cfm?#410


WEEK'S TOP NEWS ...

eRate bust signals crackdown
At least 26 cases of suspected eRate abuse are currently under
investigation by the Federal Communications Commission (FCC), eSchool News
has learned. The widening probe follows a criminal complaint of an eRate
service provide who had been working with as many as 200 schools in New
York....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/news/showStoryalert.cfm?ArticleID=4194

Study probes technology’s effect on math and science achievement
When used effectively, computer drills and tutorials can improve student
performance in math and science—but the benefits of computer simulations
and electronic sensors are less tangible, at least in studies that have
been conducted so far, according to a research review that the National
Science Foundation (NSF) plans to release this spring....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/news/showStoryalert.cfm?ArticleID=4192

Maine laptop access expanded to poorer students’ homes
Thousands of Maine students will receive free home internet access for
laptop computers assigned by their schools, thanks to millions of dollars
worth of cash and in-kind donations, outgoing Gov. Angus King has
announced....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/news/showStoryalert.cfm?ArticleID=4193

Mississippi puts an online computer in every classroom
In a milestone for student achievement and state pride, Mississippi has
become one of the first states to have an online computer in each of its
public-school classrooms, a spokesman for the governor said....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/news/showStoryalert.cfm?ArticleID=4190



MORE GRANT DEADLINES ... 
$2.5 million to increase girls' participation in science, technology, and
math
Deadline: Jan.23
http://www.eschoolnews.com/resources/funding/opps.cfm?#411


$5,000+ for projects in science, math, and technology education
Deadline: Feb. 1
http://www.eschoolnews.com/resources/funding/opps.cfm?#294


$54,000 in awards, grants, and scholarships for school libraries
Deadline: Feb. 3 
http://www.eschoolnews.com/resources/funding/opps.cfm?#280



SITE OF THE WEEK ... 
Discover the living histories of influential African-Americans
From the National Visionary Leadership Project (NVLP) comes a venue for
students to explore the accomplishments and inspiring true-life stories of
70 living African-American legends. The web site complements an ambitious
historical project that includes live conferences, lesson plans, and
mentoring programs....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/resources/links/showLink.cfm?linkID=100


SPECIAL FEATURE ... 
eSN's 3rd Annual Tech-Savvy Superintendent Awards
In our third annual Tech-Savvy Superintendent Awards, eSchool News
recognized 10 of the nation’s top K-12 executives for their outstanding
leadership and vision in the area of educational technology. Find out who
was chosen by the editors of eSchool News with help from last year’s
winners....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/news/showStoryalert.cfm?ArticleID=4189


PARTNERS UPDATE ... 
CDI computer dealers organize technology discount for multiple schools
At a time when budgets are squeezed tight and schools have had many
monetary issues to deal with at the start of a new school year, one school
board successfully acquired state-of-the art computer technology at a
reduced cost by collaborating with 30 of its member schools....
http://www.eschoolnews.com/resources/partners/showrelease.cfm?ReleaseID=321



Free Content for Your Site!


Would you like to include the latest breaking school technology news on
your school's website...for FREE?

It's free and easy to get started, and all the news headlines are
automatically posted on your site once you sign up.
Just visit our free content page at www.eschoolnews.com/exchange and sign
up.
http://www.eschoolnews.com/exchange


